# 6. はやる心

Princess: “——————...♪”
Princess: “No, he's miles and miles away in a different country. He'll never hear me if I keep singing like a squeaky songbird...”
Princess: “After giving me so much courage too...”
Princess: “He told me that he liked the way I sing, so I have to make sure my voice reaches him!”
Princess: “————♪ ————♪”
Audience: Wow... Her voice is so pretty...
Audience: This is her first time playing the lead, right? She looks so poised...
Princess: “————♪”
Nene: (My voice wavered there a little...)
Nene: (The audience seems to be reacting okay, but I can't be happy with just this...)
Nene: (I need to do a better job of moving their hearts...!)
Princess: “————♪ ————♪”
Director: Nice work with the last show, everyone. Overall, each performance went really well, and the audience seemed to enjoy everything.
Director: This is the result of all the hard work you put in day in and day out. Let's keep doing our best and make our next show just as good!
Troupe Members: Yeah!
Nene: (Each performance went really well, huh...?)
Nene: (That's good to hear. I'm glad we were able to get through them all...)
Director: Kusanagi.
Nene: Oh, Mr. Amemiya, hello...
Amemiya: Nice work out there. I wanted to congratulate our star as the director of this troupe.
Nene: I see... Thank you for going out of your way to do this.
Amemiya: You just seem to keep finding ways to get better, Kusanagi...
Amemiya: When you first joined us, you were pretty rough around the edges. But now, you're regularly competing for leading roles.
Amemiya: Naturally, you still have a lot of growth potential... But I have to say, Kazamatsuri brought us a real gem.
Nene: Oh...
Nene: Thank you very much.
Nene: I plan on doing even more moving forward in order to win those roles.
Amemiya: Yes, I'll be looking forward to seeing how you grow.
Nene: (I can't be happy with just having a lot of growth potential...)
Nene: (I mean, I've auditioned for countless roles... And just finally managed to become the lead for one show.)
Nene: (I have to keep getting better and better. Or else...)
Nene: (I won't be able to go overseas like those two...)
Troupe Member A: Mr. Amemiya! Kusanagi! We want to throw an after-party! Are you two free to join us?
Nene: An after-party?
Troupe Member A: Yes, we wanted to give ourselves a big pat on the back! So, we're looking for people who are free to go.
Amemiya: Ah, that sounds fun. I think I'll go. What about you, Kusanagi?
Nene: Oh, umm...
Nene: I really appreciate the invitation, but I think I'll pass. Please go on without me.
Troupe Member B: Wait, Kusanagi, are you gonna head back and practice the way you always do?
Nene: I am. I start getting antsy if I don't since it's basically a part of my routine at this point.
Nene: Plus, our next show is just around the corner.
Troupe Member B: Oh, that's right. Yuka Kazamatsuri agreed to appear as a guest star, right?!
Troupe Member C: I know that she and Mr. Amemiya used to be in the same troupe, but I still can't believe she's coming back to Japan to perform in this show.
Nene: Me neither... I'm excited since she's my hero.
Troupe Member B: Right. But you just finished doing a show, so don't push yourself too hard, okay?
Nene: I'll be careful. Anyway, nice work, everyone.
Nene: “Please put down your sword. I'd rather not see you all covered in blood.”
Nene: “And I'm sure your late mother wouldn't have wanted to see you in this state.”
Nene: That didn't feel right...
Nene: Natalie should know exactly why her childhood friend made the decision to go into battle.
Nene: Which means she wouldn't just be trying to stop her at all costs. She should be feeling pretty conflicted.
Nene: So, maybe I can try making my voice waver...
Nene: “Please put down your sword... I'd rather not see you all covered in blood.”
Nene: “And I'm sure your late mother wouldn't have wanted to see you in this state.”
Nene: ... Let's take a look at that video I just took of myself.
Nene: (My voice sounds more like how I thought it should, but the way I'm moving still looks kinda funny...)
Nene: (She's torn between wanting to respect her friend's wishes and hoping to stop her from going. In order to clearly express that internal conflict...)
Nene: That really startled me... I totally forgot to turn off notifications.
Nene: Emu sent me a message...?
Nene: (Come to think of it, she said she wanted to throw a farewell party for Rui and Tsukasa. I wonder where we're doing that...)
Nene: Phoenix Wonderland...?
Nene: I see... We're doing it there.
Nene: I guess it is the perfect place for us to gather.
Nene: (Wherever they are right now, they're all doing their best.)
Nene: (Which means I also need to keep practicing.)
???: <I want you to be the one to figure out what's truly best for you.>
???: <And I'll do whatever I can to help you find that answer.>
???: <It won't be easy, but doing your best by working together as a team to get through this will do wonders for you in the future.>
Nene: (Huh...?)
Nene: (Who said that just now...?)
Yuka: Oh, Nene, it's been so long...!
Nene: Huh...? M-Ms. Kazamatsuri?! What are you doing here...?
Yuka: I got back to Japan a little while ago. Amemiya let me know his troupe would be throwing an after-party today and invited me to join. He wanted to introduce me to everyone.
Yuka: That's where I heard that you were probably still practicing, Nene. So, I'm here.
Nene: I see...
Nene: It's so nice to see you again.
Nene: And I'm really looking forward to performing in that show with you!
Yuka: *Nod* I'm also looking forward to working with you.
Yuka: Have you been taking breaks, Nene...?
Nene: Huh? Oh, yes... I've been taking quick breathers here and there while checking over the videos I've been taking of myself...
Yuka: Haha. Amemiya was right. You really do have an incredible work ethic.
Yuka: But you need to take proper breaks. To be perfectly honest, you look pretty tired.
Nene: I do? I'll be careful...
Yuka: Anyway, now that I've had a chance to see you, Nene, I'm going to head back. I'd rather not be in your way for too long.
Yuka: But promise to take real breaks, okay?
Nene: O-Okay...!
Yuka: Then, I'll see you later. And don't push yourself too hard.
Nene: Thank you. I promise to be careful.
Nene: (Ms. Kazamatsuri's such a nice person.)
Nene: (She came all this way just to see me, and she expressed genuine concern...)
Nene: I have to do my best...
